integrated health promotion to maximize healthy aging events at stanford integrated health promotion to maximize healthy aging facebook twitter email print add to calendar in this 5 session course both science and practice are used to help participants design a sustained personal plan for a healthy extended and fulfilling life the class is taught by an internal medicine prevention physician and a well being practitioner we will present long standing knowledge and emerging science of impact of mind body connection exercise and social engagement on longevity class participants will integrate this to design an optimal long term personal health plan to mindfully navigate their environment through developing goal setting and problem solving skills through weekly reflections they will develop an ability to evaluate and redesign these health plans to adapt to life's changing realities instructors randall stafford md phd associate professor of medicine and director of the stanford program in prevention outcomes and practices manjula waldron phd consulting professor me design stanford university when tuesday january 31 2012 5 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where li ka shing learning ctr rm 306 map audience general public faculty staff alumni friends members tags class health wellness sponsor health improvement program contact 650 721 6003 ausserer stanford edu admission register for this 5 session class at hip stanford edu fee $200.00 stap ea funds yes class code mha 01 permalink http events stanford edu events 302 30227 more info last modified january 31 2012
